description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Contract type- Permanent&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Hours- Up to 37.5 hours per week&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for dynamic and motivated registered nurses to join the Day Unit and Extended Stay Area. We are looking for enthusiastic, forward thinking and highly motivated nurses with a genuine interest in pre and post anaesthetic care to join our dynamic and friendly team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidates will be nurses who are patient-centred focused and believe that patient experience and safety is central to the care they deliver. We are looking for individuals who are flexible, innovative and dynamic in outlook with a keen sense of team working and eager to learn.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The day unit and extended stay area offers excellent opportunities to expand your experience in surgical nursing and provides experience in treating a wide range of surgical conditions. Working in this highly motivated team will give you sound decision making skills and you will be offered development opportunities within this enthusiastic and well led team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be responsible for maintaining high standards of care whilst caring for a group of patients under the direction of the senior nurse. Surgical experience is desirable but not essential.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;In return we can offer you:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A supportive &amp; friendly working environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Active encouragement to learn and develop within your role&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Dedicated career pathways and great opportunities for continuing professional development&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Commitment to, and support for, your wellbeing&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;NHS Pension Scheme&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;NHS discount and salary sacrifice schemes, including childcare vouchers&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;What we can offer you as nurse joining our Trust&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Nurses who have completed their qualification and are awaiting NMC registration will be paid at AfC Band 4 (previously Band 2)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A £750 relocation fee where a nurse is moving 20 miles from an address that was 50 miles from your new work base;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Nurses who have completed their qualification and are awaiting NMC registration will be paid at AfC Band 5 (previously Band 4)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We would welcome any interested applicants to contact us to discuss these positions further and to arrange an informal visit if desired.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name: Lynn Ellis&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job title: Sister&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address: Lynn.Ellis@york.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number: 01904 721078&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;It&#39;s not just the area that&#39;s a great draw.  In addition, as a member of our team you’ll have access to one of the most generous and comprehensive pension schemes in the UK, a minimum of 27 days annual leave (on top of Bank Holidays) and an award-winning package of staff benefits (see link on the right).&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
